Definition: shipbuilding) the point of intersection between two vertical lines, one line through the center of buoyancy of the hull of a ship in equilibrium and the other line through the center of buoyancy of the hull when the ship is inclined to one side
Example: the distance of this intersection above the center of gravity is an indication of the stability of the ship
Synonyms: adj, pert, metacentric, metacentre, noun, location, Canada, r, Britain, intersection, act, shipbuilding, c, the, point, of, between, two, vertical, lines, one, line, through, center, buoyancy, hull, a, ship, in, equilibrium, and, other, when, is, inclined, to, side, distance, this, above, gravity, an, indication, stability
Category: noun.cognition
